                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-178-off1038 t18210912-178-crimeloc1041"></join>. On the 3d of August, about half-past three o'clock in the afternoon, I was sitting in my back parlour, and saw the prisoner in my back garden, he went into the kitchen and took three tea and one table spoon from the drawer; when he came up, I asked his business; he asked if I wanted any shavings for my stove - I said, "Yes," and he immediately ran away - I followed and caught him, he gave me a tea-spoon, and said, that was all he had taken, and hoped I would forgive him. On searching further, I found the other spoons in his basket among the shavings.</p>
